<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-10-27T11:21:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-10-27T11:21:00-05:00" n="817" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d817">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Day</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date ana="#date_imprecise-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" when="1898-10-27T16:30:00+00:09"><hi rend="italic">October 27, 1898</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 18.]</seg></opener>
                        <p>At meeting to-day Spaniards accepted our last draft articles 1 and 2 as
                            to Cuba, Puerto Rico, and Guam in exact language of protocol, expressly
                            subject to agreement being reached on all the articles which treaty
                            should contain. Then asked when we should be ready to proceed to
                            question of Philippine Islands, and on our motion adjournment had till
                            Monday for that purpose. Tuesday and Wednesday following being religious
                            holidays, understood if not ready Monday can have what further time
                            desired.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <dateline rendition="#left"><date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-10-27T16:30:00+00:09">Thursday, 4.30,
                                    afternoon</date>.</dateline>
                            <lb/>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Day.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>